<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="404" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[178,1085,688,939]" pageId="15" pageNumber="404">
Diagnosis: The male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wahis &amp; Terzo" authorityYear="1996" box="[516,623,763,784]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Ferreola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insolita">
<emphasis box="[516,623,763,784]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="404">F. insolita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by a black body with blue reflexions and with red pronotum, by a sharp edge between propodeal declivity and propodeal dorsum, and by basally transparent wings. There are no bands of pubescence on tergites. The 
<typeStatus box="[345,434,851,873]" pageId="15" pageNumber="404">holotype</typeStatus>
measures 
<quantity box="[542,616,851,872]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="15" pageNumber="404" unit="mm" value="11.0">11 mm</quantity>
. For detailed description see WAHIS &amp; TERZO (1996).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
